						<summary>

						<p>This records an endowment of 13 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by <hi rend="bold">Muṉṉūṟṟuvaṉ Tiru•••••• Avanimaṅgalyaṉ</hi> the <hi rend="italic">madhyastha</hi> of the village (name lost) in Kiḻār-kūṟṟam a subdivision of Maḻa-nāḍu to provide for the sacred bath of the god <hi rend="bold">•••• yūr-Mahādēva</hi> on the day of <hi rend="italic">Dakshiṇāyana</hi> with 108 pots of water (from the river ?) with the interest on the amount (?) <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi> 1(3/4) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and 4 <hi rend="italic">mañjāḍi.</hi> This inscription also like No. 71 above seems to have belonged to another temple. This is probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
